# .envrc
#
# direnv integration – automatically activates the Nix dev shell whenever you
# `cd` into this directory (or any subdirectory).
#
# Prerequisites
# ─────────────
#   1. Install Nix with flakes enabled:
#        https://nixos.org/download  (multi-user recommended)
#      Then add to /etc/nix/nix.conf (or ~/.config/nix/nix.conf):
#        experimental-features = nix-command flakes
#
#   2. Install direnv:
#        https://direnv.net/docs/installation.html
#      Hook it into your shell (e.g. for bash, add to ~/.bashrc):
#        eval "$(direnv hook bash)"
#
#   3. Allow this file once:
#        direnv allow
#
# After that, entering the project directory will automatically load the
# dev shell defined in flake.nix – no manual `nix develop` needed.

use flake
